## Summary

```
WARN model_discovery: kimi_coding refresh failed: HTTP 401
WARN model_discovery: minimax refresh failed: HTTP 401
WARN model_discovery: zai_coding refresh failed: HTTP 401
```

Each refresh attempt 401s — meaning the API key configured for these
providers does not authenticate against their /v1/models (or equivalent)
discovery endpoint. Chat-completion calls TO the same providers work
(MiniMax shows successful 200 responses elsewhere in the log), so the
key is valid for chat but not for discovery — likely a scope/endpoint
mismatch.

## Suggested next steps

1. Verify each provider's discovery endpoint and whether it requires
   a different auth header style (e.g., `Authorization: Bearer` vs
   `x-api-key`). Some Anthropic-compat services accept the chat header
   on /messages but not on /models.
2. If the endpoint genuinely requires a separate token (e.g. an org/admin
   key), document that — and either gracefully degrade discovery to the
   built-in catalog or surface a one-time config warning rather than
   recurring WARN spam.
3. Suppress repeated 401 WARNs after the first per process — once it's
   known to 401, retrying every 12h adds nothing to the log.

## Evidence

- ~/.clawq/daemon.log: search 'model_discovery.*refresh failed' — 3
  distinct providers, each WARN appears once per startup cycle